\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 22. G. concatenatum} Cosson,{\i  Not. Pl. Crit.} 38 (1849). Like {\b 20} but stems 20-65 cm, more or less erect, not much branched at the base; leaves 15-22 × 1-3 mm, linear to narrowly lanceolate, acute, glabrous or scabrid above, glabrous or papillose beneath, the margin usually not recurved as far as the midrib; corolla 1·5-2·5 mm, shallowly infundibuliform; tube 0·4-1 mm; lobes 1-1·2 mm, acute. {\i Open habitats. S.W. Spain, S.E. Portugal.} Hs Lu. ({\i Morocco, Algeria.})
