\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 25. G. tunetanum} Lam.,{\i  Encycl. Méth. Bot.}{\b  2}: 583 (1788).Stems 30-80 cm, erect, not much branched. Leaves 20-25 × 1-1·5 mm, shortly awned, shining, shortly hairy and rough above, tomentose beneath; margin usually recurved to the midrib. Inflorescence ovoid-elongate. Corolla 3-3·5 mm in diameter, hairy externally; lobes apiculate. Fruit densely hairy, very rarely glabrous. {\i Dry places. S. Spain; Sicilia.} Hs Si. ({\i N.W. Africa.})
\par 

